'''''Empire: Wargame of the Century''''' is a video game based on ''[[Empire (1977 video game)|Empire]]'' developed by [[Walter Bright]] and published by Interstel Corporation in 1987.

==Development==
{{Unreferenced section|date=July 2020}}
[[Walter Bright]] recoded his 1977 mainframe game ''[[Empire (1977 video game)|Empire]]'' in [[C (programming language)|C]] on an [[IBM Personal Computer|IBM PC]]. With low commercial expectations, he submitted an announcement to January 1984 ''[[Byte (magazine)|BYTE]]'' magazine<nowiki>'</nowiki>s "Software Received" section, and received a flood of orders. After writing to many software companies (including [[Broderbund]], [[Sirius Software]], [[Simon & Schuster]], [[Sublogic]], [[Epyx]], and [[MicroProse]]), he licensed the game to a small software company named Interstel. Mark Baldwin was brought in to coauthor the game redesigning it for the commercial market. Starting around 1987, ''Empire: Wargame of the Century'' on the [[Atari ST]],<ref>
